<snippet>
	<content><![CDATA[const defaults = (obj, ...defs) => Object.assign({}, obj, ...defs.reverse(), obj);]]></content>
	<description>Assigns default values for all properties in an object that are `undefined`.  Use `Object.assign()` to create a new empty object and copy the original one to maintain key order, use `Array.reverse()` and the spread operator `...` to combine the default values from left to right, finally use `obj` again to overwrite properties that originally had a value.</description>
